@node introduction "Introduction"

Introduction
------------

  NIS (Nihongo Input System) is a front end preprocessor for the Amiga
  Computer to allow input of Japanese language text.

  It currently allows the entry of ascii, jis double width ascii, and
  kana text, both hiragana and katakana (using romaji entry, on-the-fly
  conversion into hiragana).

  The registered version will contain some form of kanji lookup.

@endnode

